        <name xml:lang="en">potassium chloride</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The exchange has been updated from 'potassium chloride, as K2O' into 'potassium chloride' and therefore its amount has been scaled (multiplied) from 0.9614 kg by 1.5829 kg of 'potassium chloride' per kg of 'potassium chloride, as K2O'. Original comment of the exchange is: Represents 1.5253 kg of KCl. Pure potassium chloride, recorded as  potassium oxide (K2O) equivalents. Potassium-containing fertilizers are expressed as the amount of K2O needed to acquire the amount of potassium present in the fertilizer.</comment>
